  <description><![CDATA[<p>Over the years the impressive Grand Hotel Toplice has been favoured by the rich and the famous and, from its lake-front position, offers fairy tale views of <a data-udi="umb://document/e0872feec9b24b8db1b30d83108b172e" href="/{localLink:umb://document/e0872feec9b24b8db1b30d83108b172e}" title="Lake Bled">Lake Bled</a> and the surrounding mountains - it's the only hotel in Bled that stands right at the lake's edge.</p>
<h2>Beautifully furnished and traditional in style</h2>
<p>Elegant design, refined comfort, high standards of service, and excellent cuisine all define this popular hotel. Bedrooms are comfortable and well-equipped, and many have a balcony and lake view.</p>
<h2>Wild swimming in Lake Bled</h2>
<p>The beautiful Luisa Spa has an indoor pool fed by a natural thermal spring - the mineral-rich waters are said to promote health and well-being. The spa also has Finnish, Turkish, and infrared saunas, as well as a range of spa and massage treatments (payable locally). At the bottom of the garden is a private lido and a lake swimming area - you can rent rowing boats and paddle boards from here, too.</p>]]></description>
